nts doesn't have a configuration option for that. This means that this issue occurs in non-admin accounts! :)\n\nMay we reopen this report?\n\nThanks\n-Ahsan","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2016-07-03T17:36:32.098Z","updated_at":"2016-07-03T17:36:32.098Z","actor":{"username":"ahsan","cleared":false,"url":"/ahsan","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/048/674/a85d1f36a4d4b4c6269951bc913cc6f4fc3fcb23_original.JPG/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"paragonie","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":1051396,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"\u003e This means that this issue occurs in non-admin accounts! :)\n\nLet's try this again.\n\nMost configuration options can only be set by administrator users, but affects all users.\n\nThe reason for this is simple: In my experience, administrators are more responsible than casual users. If you burden most people with \"should we log other devices out if our password is ever reset?\" they'll opt for convenience. Someone responsible with running a website is going to actually weigh the security and usability trade-offs and make the decision most appropriate for their risk profile.\n\nInstead of just blind-testing cspr.ng and reporting \"missing best practice\" issues you find, you'll find your time better spent looking at the source code and verifying that a feature is missing rather than not enabled.","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2016-07-03T17:41:46.183Z","updated_at":"2016-07-03T17:41:46.183Z","actor":{"username":"paragonie-scott","cleared":false,"url":"/paragonie-scott","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/051/441/089de22b2f1b80a1e57a2792318dede5cbad81db_original.png/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"paragonie","actor_is_team_member":true,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":1051399,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Hey @paragonie-scott,\nI am not just 'blind-testing' cspr.ng, I've tried every thing in a non-admin account, but there isn't any option like 'logout of other devices after password change' this is a valid session issue, not just a \"missing best practice\", my report is actually about that there 'should' be an option like 'logout of other devices after password change' or after password change, other sessions should automatically get destroyed for non-admin accounts!\n\nThere isn't any kind of protection for this issue in *non-admin* accounts! :)\n\nThanks\n-Ahsan","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2016-07-03T17:47:39.804Z","updated_at":"2016-07-03T17:47:39.804Z","actor":{"username":"ahsan","cleared":false,"url":"/ahsan","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/048/674/a85d1f36a4d4b4c6269951bc913cc6f4fc3fcb23_original.JPG/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"paragonie","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":1051401,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"\u003e There isn't any kind of protection for this issue in non-admin accounts! :)\n\nYes there is.\n\nIf the admin enables it, the protection applies to non-admin accounts. Therefore, there is \"any kind of protection for this issue in non-admin accounts\", it's just not up to non-admins to enable it or not.","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2016-07-03T17:51:37.861Z","updated_at":"2016-07-03T17:51:37.861Z","actor":{"username":"paragonie-scott","cleared":false,"url":"/paragonie-scott","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/051/441/089de22b2f1b80a1e57a2792318dede5cbad81db_original.png/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"paragonie","actor_is_team_member":true,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":1051403,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Yes, there is protection, but non-admins should be allowed to enable/disable it!\n\n","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2016-07-03T17:53:18.542Z","updated_at":"2016-07-03T17:53:18.542Z","actor":{"username":"ahsan","cleared":false,"url":"/ahsan","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/048/674/a85d1f36a4d4b4c6269951bc913cc6f4fc3fcb23_original.JPG/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"paragonie","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":1051405,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Answered above:\n\n\u003e  In my experience, administrators are more responsible than casual users. If you burden most people with \"should we log other devices out if our password is ever reset?\" they'll opt for convenience. Someone responsible with running a website is going to actually weigh the security and usability trade-offs and make the decision most appropriate for their risk profile.","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2016-07-03T17:58:05.163Z","updated_at":"2016-07-03T17:58:05.163Z","actor":{"username":"paragonie-scott","cleared":false,"url":"/paragonie-scott","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/051/441/089de22b2f1b80a1e57a2792318dede5cbad81db_original.png/fd4